data.content:
Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`. Both work without any special flags:

```csharp
Span<nint> signed = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

On this 64-bit system, `nint.Size` is 8 bytes. The native-sized integer types (`nint`/`nuint`, introduced in C# 9) are valid `stackalloc` element types just like `int` or `long`.
